acceptNomination(string,string).details: Requires the sender to be nominated before accepting.

balanceOfBatch(address[],uint256[]).details: See {IERC1155-balanceOfBatch}. Requirements: - `accounts` and `ids` must have the same length.

returns._0: The URI of the contract-level metadata.

params.organizerId: The ID of the organizer to deregister.

params.organizerAddress: The wallet address of the organizer.

returns.bio: The biography or description of the organizer.
returns.name: The name of the organizer.
returns.wallet: The wallet address associated with the organizer.

params._referralModuleAddress: Address of the ReferralModule to interact with referral functionalities.
params.initialOwner: The address to be set as the owner of the contract.

returns._0: bool True if the address is a registered organizer, false otherwise.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params.newURI: The new URI string to be set.
params.tokenId: The token ID for which to set the URI.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

params.name: New name for the organizer.
params.organizerId: The ID of the organizer to update.
params.wallet: New wallet address for the organizer.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

params.tokenId: The token ID of the artist.

returns._0: The URI associated with the artist token.

acceptNomination(string,string).notice: Accepts a nomination for organizer status.

contractURI().notice: Retrieves the URI for the contract metadata.

deregisterOrganizer(uint256).notice: Deregisters an organizer, burning their token and removing their registration.

getOrganizer(address).notice: Retrieves organizer information by wallet address.

initialize(address,address).notice: Initializes the contract with metadata URI and ReferralModule address.

isOrganizerRegistered(address).notice: Checks if an address is a registered organizer.

nominate(address).notice: Nominates an address for organizer status using a referral credit.

nominatedOrganizers(address).notice: Tracks whether a given address has been nominated to become an organizer.

setContractURI(string).notice: Sets or updates the URI for a specific artist token.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).notice: Sets the URI for a specific token.

updateOrganizer(uint256,string,string,ad.notice: Updates the profile information of an organizer.

uri(uint256).notice: Retrieves the URI for a specific artist's token.
